<div class="container mx-auto py-8">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-theme-primary">E-sika Theme System</h1>

  <p class="mb-6 text-lg text-theme-secondary">
    This page demonstrates the centralized theme system for the E-sika application.
    The theme is implemented using CSS variables and utility classes, without modifying the tailwind.config.js file.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-theme-primary rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How to Use the Theme</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">1. Theme Variables</h3>
        <p>Use CSS variables for consistent styling:</p>
        <pre class="bg-theme-secondary p-4 rounded-md mt-2 overflow-x-auto">
color: rgb(var(--color-primary-500) / 1);
font-size: var(--text-lg);
padding: var(--spacing-4);
border-radius: var(--radius-md);
        </pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">2. Theme Utility Classes</h3>
        <p>Use the provided utility classes:</p>
        <pre class="bg-theme-secondary p-4 rounded-md mt-2 overflow-x-auto">
&lt;div class="text-primary-500 bg-secondary-100 p-4 rounded-lg shadow-md"&gt;
  Content with theme styling
&lt;/div&gt;
        </pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">3. Theme Components</h3>
        <p>Use the predefined component classes:</p>
        <pre class="bg-theme-secondary p-4 rounded-md mt-2 overflow-x-auto">
&lt;button class="theme-btn theme-btn-primary"&gt;Primary Button&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;div class="theme-card"&gt;
  &lt;div class="theme-card-header"&gt;Card Title&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="theme-card-body"&gt;Card content&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
        </pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">4. Dark Mode Support</h3>
        <p>The theme system includes built-in dark mode support:</p>
        <pre class="bg-theme-secondary p-4 rounded-md mt-2 overflow-x-auto">
&lt;!-- Use theme utility classes that automatically adapt to the current theme --&gt;
&lt;div class="bg-theme-primary text-theme-primary"&gt;
  This content adapts to the current theme
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- Or use Tailwind's dark mode classes --&gt;
&lt;div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-black dark:text-white"&gt;
  This content adapts to dark mode
&lt;/div&gt;
        </pre>
        <p class="mt-2">Toggle dark mode using the button in the header.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%= render 'shared/theme_example' %>
</div>
